long.} 17. bxc3 Nxe4 {For the exchange Black has a pawn and strong center, but
his next moves are not optimal.} 18. Bb2 Ndf6 (18... f5 $1 {[%csl Rc2,Rc3,Gd6,
Ge4,Ge5,Gf5] to get a firm grip in the center was preferable.}) 19. c4 Qc8 {
